=== {{IRN}} ===
{{main|伊朗网络审查}}
[[2009年伊朗总统选举|2009年伊朗总统选举]]后，因为担心Facebook进行反对派运动，该网站被封锁<ref name="iran">{{Cite web |title=Facebook Faces Censorship in Iran |url=http://www.hamsaweb.org/crime/4.html |accessdate=2008-04-30 |date=2007-08-29 |publisher=American Islamic Congress |language=en |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080424001859/http://www.hamsaweb.org/crime/4.html |archivedate=2008-04-24 |trans_title=Facebook在伊朗面对审查 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。然而截至2013年9月，封锁Facebook四年后没有另行通知，Twitter和Facebook据认为被解封<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://mashable.com/2013/09/16/twitter-facebook-iran/ |title=Iran Unblocks Twitter and Facebook |date=2013-09-17 |work=Chris Taylor |accessdate=203-09-17 |agency=[[Mashable|Mashable]] |language=en |trans_title=伊朗对Twitter和Facebook解除封锁 |archive-date=2017-08-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170829214714/http://mashable.com/2013/09/16/twitter-facebook-iran/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。但是解封的隔天，即星期二，伊朗再次无法正常访问Facebook和Twitter，引起人们质疑解除封禁是故意的，还是因为技术故障的问题<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2013/09/18/world/middleeast/facebook-and-twitter-blocked-again-in-iran-after-respite.html |title=Iran Bars Social Media Again After a Day |last=Erdbrink |first=Thomas |date=2013-09-17 |publisher=The New York Times |accessdate=2013-12-10 |language=en |trans_title=伊朗一日后又再次禁止访问社交媒体 |archive-date=2017-12-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171216204003/http://www.nytimes.com/2013/09/18/world/middleeast/facebook-and-twitter-blocked-again-in-iran-after-respite.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== {{flag|毛里求斯}} ===
2007年11月8日，因为Facebook的有关假冒总理的个人主页，[[毛里求斯|毛里求斯]]资讯通信科技管理局随即下令全国的[[互联网服务供应商|互联网服务供应商]]封锁[[Facebook|Facebook]]。翌日，毛里求斯恢复了Facebook的访问<ref>{{Cite web |title=Facebook: A Mauritian tragedy? |url=http://www.noulakaz.net/weblog/2007/11/08/facebook-a-mauritian-tragedy/ |accessdate=2011-10-29 |date=2007-11-08 |publisher=Noulakaz |language=en |trans_title=Facebook：毛里求斯的悲剧？ |archive-date=2011-07-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110723230916/http://www.noulakaz.net/weblog/2007/11/08/facebook-a-mauritian-tragedy/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Facebook outage in Mauritius – it's been censored!!! |url=http://pascalg.wordpress.com/2007/11/08/facebook-outage-in-mauritius-its-been-censored/ |accessdate=2011-10-29 |date=2007-11-08 |publisher=Pascalg.wordpress.com |language=en |trans_title=毛里求斯封禁并审查Facebook |archive-date=2011-08-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110824024531/http://pascalg.wordpress.com/2007/11/08/facebook-outage-in-mauritius-its-been-censored/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Maurice censure le site communautaire «Facebook» |url=http://www.lexpress.mu/services/archive-97239-maurice-censure-le-site-communautaire-facebook.html |accessdate=2013-12-10 |date=2007-11-09 |publisher=L'express |language=fr |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120913202342/http://www.lexpress.mu/services/archive-97239-maurice-censure-le-site-communautaire-facebook.html |archivedate=2012-09-13 |trans_title=毛里求斯审查社交网站Facebook |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。

=== {{flag|摩洛哥}} ===
2008年2月5日，摩洛哥公民{{link-en|摩洛哥假冒王子事件|Fouad Mourtada affair|福阿德·穆尔塔达}}涉嫌创建Facebook个人主页假冒[[穆莱·拉希德王子|穆莱·拉希德王子]]而被捕<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.cnn.com/2008/WORLD/africa/02/07/morocco.facebook/index.html?eref=rss_latest |title=Police arrest man for 'villainous' theft of prince's ID on Facebook |date=February 7, 2008 |publisher=CNN |accessdate=March 5, 2008 |language=en |trans_title=警方以在Facebook假冒王子身份的罪名将男子逮捕 |archive-date=2018-10-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181005043913/http://www.cnn.com/2008/WORLD/africa/02/07/morocco.facebook/index.html?eref=rss_latest |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2008/02/07/world/africa/07briefs-identity.html?ex=1360040400&en=28cce9bbc525d4cd&ei=5088&partner=rssnyt&emc=rss |title=Morocco: Man Held in Alleged Royal Identity Theft |date=2008-02-07 |publisher=The New York Times |accessdate=2008-03-05 |language=en |trans_title=摩洛哥男子涉嫌假冒皇族身份被捕 |archive-date=2019-02-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190219015453/https://www.nytimes.com/2008/02/07/world/africa/07briefs-identity.html?ex=1360040400&en=28cce9bbc525d4cd&ei=5088&partner=rssnyt&emc=rss |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== {{DPRK}} ===
朝鮮是局內網，政府對所有外國網站進行物理封鎖，Facebook同樣不例外，不过外国人可以通过接入[[朝鲜互联网|朝鲜互联网]]的形式访问。2016年4月4日，朝鲜政府正式宣布屏蔽Facebook，并表示任何试图破解的人士将受到朝鲜法律的惩罚<ref name="DPRK">{{Cite news |url=http://finance.sina.com.cn/world/gjcj/2016-04-05/doc-ifxqxcnp8544317.shtml |title=朝鲜开始正式屏蔽脸书推特等网站 |date=2016年4月4日 |publisher=新浪新闻 |accessdate=2016年4月4日 |archive-date=2021年2月9日 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210209155743/http://finance.sina.com.cn/world/gjcj/2016-04-05/doc-ifxqxcnp8544317.shtml |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== {{SYR}} ===
叙利亚政府声称Facebook促进对当局的攻击，因而禁止该网站<ref name="syria">{{Cite news |url=http://www.reuters.com/article/worldNews/idUSOWE37285020071123 |title=Syria blocks Facebook in Internet crackdown |author=Khaled Yacoub Oweis |date=2007-11-23 |publisher=Reuters |accessdate=2008-03-05 |language=en |trans_title=叙利亚封锁Facebook镇压互联网 |archive-date=2007-11-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071127114519/http://www.reuters.com/article/worldNews/idUSOWE37285020071123 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.jpost.com/Middle-East/Syrian-govt-blocks-use-of-Facebook |title=Syrian gov't blocks use of Facebook |date=2007-11-24 |work=[[耶路撒冷邮报|耶路撒冷邮报]] |accessdate=2008-03-08 |language=en |trans_title=叙利亚政府禁止Facebook的使用 |archive-date=2017-03-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170301180845/http://www.jpost.com/Middle-East/Syrian-govt-blocks-use-of-Facebook |dead-url=no }}</ref>。政府也担心[[以色列情報及特殊使命局|以色列]]在Facebook入侵叙利亚社交网络<ref name="syria" />。叙利亚公民也利用Facebook批评[[叙利亚政府|叙利亚政府]]，因为公开批评叙利亚政府曾可被监禁<ref name="syria" />。2011年2月，所有[[互联网服务供应商|互联网服务供应商]]解除对Facebook的封锁，该网站仍可访问。

